    "body": "Fixes pytorch/pytorch#180908.\r\n\r\nCompiling certain kernels on Triton 3.7 fails with `RuntimeError: PassManager::run failed` and no diagnostic. The trigger is any IR that reaches `RemoveLayoutConversions` cleanup with roughly ten or more unrolled `scf.if` regions carrying tensor values — e.g. `tl.static_range(N>=10)` with a runtime guard around a loop-carried vector accumulator. vLLM's `_penalties_kernel` at `MAX_SPEC_LEN=10` is the original reported issue and falls under this\r\n\r\nWe bisected the LLVM range to commit [`cf9b3bbb0986`](https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/commit/cf9b3bbb0986) (\"[mlir][IR][NFC] Add `RewriterBase::eraseOpResults` convenience helper\",\r\nPR #174152), which rewrote `scf.if`'s `RemoveUnusedResults` to use the new helper. Adjacent-commit measurement on a single trigger kernel showed the killer-cleanup iteration count flipping from 2 to 11 across that commit; we believe that the new pattern emits notifications in an order the greedy rewriter can't batch on chain-shaped inputs. For ten chained `scf.if`s that's eleven iterations vs MLIR's default cap of ten — just past the cap.\r\n\r\nThe pass's final cleanup site previously ran `ConvertLayoutOp`,`scf.For`, and `scf.If` canonicalizations together in a single shared budget. This PR splits that into three sequential calls: first`ConvertLayoutOp` strict, then `scf.For` + `scf.If` lenient (allowed to bail with a one-line stderr breadcrumb), then `ConvertLayoutOp` re-run strict to catch simplifications unblocked by the SCF cleanup. `scf.For` shares the lenient bucket with `scf.If` because both implement `RegionBranchOpInterface`; we have no measured failure for `scf.For` today and are being conservative.\r\n\r\nTested change on minimal triton only script that reproed the issue as well as vLLM penalties_kernel on SM89 as reported in the original issue and verified problem is fixed\r\n\r\n# New contributor declaration\r\n\r\n- [x] I am not making a trivial change, such as fixing a typo in a comment.\r\n- [x] I have written a PR description following these\r\n  [rules](https://cbea.ms/git-commit/#why-not-how).\r\n- [x] I have run `pre-commit run --from-ref origin/main --to-ref HEAD`.\r\n\r\n- Select one of the following.\r\n  - [x] I have not added any tests.\r\n\r\n- Select one of the following.\r\n  - [ ] I have not added any `lit` tests.\r\n  - [x] The `lit` tests I have added follow these [best practices](https://mlir.llvm.org/getting_started/TestingGuide/#filecheck-best-practices),\r\n    including the \"tests should be minimal\" section. (Usually running Python code\r\n    and using the instructions it generates is not minimal.)\r\n\r\ncc @njriasan\r\n",
